                <div class="border rounded border-danger p-5">
                    <h1 class="projectHeader">YelpCamp</h1>
                    <p>YelpCamp was created as a training exercise for learning back-end stacks. The idea is a review
                        site for campgrounds where users can add new campgrounds, review and comment on existing
                        campgrounds and edit campgrounds they have posted. The campground data sits in a Mongo database
                        and all components have full CRUD functionality. Middleware exists in Express to handle
                        authentication and authorization for those CRUD capabilities. The site should be live shortly
                        once user management is fully completed. Currently any user can sign up any number of times
                        without any validation.</p>
